{"word":"πόλις","slug":"πόλις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>πόλις, εως, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Skt.\">Skt.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ assoc.\">assoc.</a>] a term applied to a population center, whose size or number of inhabitants could range broadly<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp> city, town <a href='B:470 2:23'>Mt 2:23</a>; <a href='B:470 10:5'>10:5</a>; <a href='B:480 11:19'>Mk 11:19</a>; <a href='B:490 2:39'>Lk 2:39</a>; <a href='B:490 8:1'>8:1</a>; <a href='B:490 10:12'>10:12</a>; <a href='B:500 1:44'>J 1:44</a>; <a href='B:500 19:20'>19:20</a>; <a href='B:510 8:5'>Ac 8:5</a>; <a href='B:510 16:12'>16:12</a>; <a href='B:520 16:23'>Ro 16:23</a>; <a href='B:540 11:32'>2 Cor 11:32</a>; <a href='B:650 13:14'>Hb 13:14</a>; <a href='B:660 4:13'>Js 4:13</a>; <a href='B:680 2:6'>2 Pt 2:6</a>; <a href='B:720 1:1'>Jd 7</a>; <a href='B:730 16:19'>Rv 16:19</a>.</b> In imagery <b><a href='B:650 12:22'>Hb 12:22</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> the symbolism <b><a href='B:730 11:8'>Rv 11:8</a>; <a href='B:730 18:10'>18:10</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in R<b>v.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> by metonymy, <b>inhabitants <a href='B:470 8:34'>Mt 8:34</a>; <a href='B:470 12:25'>12:25</a>; <a href='B:470 21:10'>21:10</a>; <a href='B:480 1:33'>Mk 1:33</a>; <a href='B:510 14:21'>Ac 14:21</a>; <a href='B:510 21:30'>21:30</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:πόλεμος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:πολιτάρχης\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}